title: MAR 07 2022 - BIDEN ADMINISTRATION FOREIGN POLICY FAILURES
description:
In a Sunday interview, the Biden administration’s Secretary of State Anthony Blinken says the U.S. has given the “green light” for NATO to provide Ukraine with fighter jets. All of this, as U.S. officials travel to Venezuela, Russia’s ally, to discuss exporting oil to the United States. Meanwhile, Bill Clinton announces the relaunch of the Clinton Global Initiative signaling a potential third presidential run for Hillary Clinton come 2024. The Supreme Court reinstates Boston Marathon Bomber’s death sentence. Ukrainian-born actress, Mila Kunis and “proud” husband Ashton Kutcher pledge $3 million dollars to GoFundMe campaign for Ukrainian relief. 


Here’s your Daily dose of Human Events with @JackPosobiec
